<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="433" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,602,807]" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,602,627]" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of eyes naked, absent arolia and black and yellow metasoma distinguishes 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pachyanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salamens">P. salamens</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[255,267,639,662]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">e</emphasis>
</emphasis>
from all 
<taxonomicName box="[398,581,638,663]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pachyanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[398,581,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Pachyanthidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except other members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[969,1075,638,663]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatum">cordatum</taxonomicName>
species-group. Males can be distinguished from others in its species group by the combination of dorsum of mesosoma rimmed laterally and posteriorly by a white band and five similar mandibular teeth. T7 with broad, apically truncate posteromedian projection that is longer than the narrow lateral spines, truncate distally and two–thirds as wide as the concavity between it and the lateral spines (
<figureCitation box="[525,608,782,807]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,862,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,860,1904]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 21. Male of Pachyanthidium salamense (Friese). a – b. Habitus. c. Face. d. T 6 – T 7." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344725/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion box="[628,662,783,806]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="32" pageNumber="433">No</collectingRegion>
females were available for study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
